						<div class="postbody">I have the Verilog complete for a stock version of the FME7 mapper and a test bench for it. As this my first Verilog design I would really appreciate someone with some experience reviewing the code.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://nesdev1.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/mappers/fme7_stock.v" class="postlink">Module Source</a>
<br /><a href="http://nesdev1.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/mappers/fme7_stock_tb.v" class="postlink">Test Bench Source</a>
<br />
<br />Also, the design will not fit into a $5 144 cell chip. It comes in at 152 cells. I've done what I can to try and reduce this, but without much experience I am not sure of what I can and cannot do. This will be a major issue for production boards as the next step up chip is $15, or we would have to use a chip from a different family that would need 5V level translation on the inputs.</div>

