					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">qbradq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Honestly what lead me to this mapper is that I am trying to create an 8-way scrolling engine using UNROM, but I wanted to use one-screen mirroring.</div><br />If that's all you want, you can do like Rare: give up the fixed bank at $C000 and use mapper 7. But then your DPCM capability becomes even more limited, as you have to repeat the sample data in all banks.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I think this is a good compromise. It provides more functionality that any of the discreet mappers or MMC1, yet will (probably) still fit into an affordable CPLD for production carts.</div>
<br />I agree.</div>

